### [Matthew Chapter 4](../../../bib/kjv/mat004.htm#001.md)

[Matthew 4:1](../../../bib/kjv/mat004.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">mat 4:1</span></span>

Then was Jesus

The temptation of Christ, the "last Adam" ([Co1
15:45](../../../bib/kjv/co1015.htm#045).md) is best understood when
contrasted with that of the "first man Adam." Adam was tempted in his
place of lord of creation, a lordship with but one reservation, the
knowledge of good and evil; ([Gen
1:26](../../../bib/kjv/gen001.htm#026).md); ([Gen
2:16-17](../../../bib/kjv/gen002.htm#016).md). Through the woman he was
tempted to add that also to his dominion. Falling, he lost all. But
Christ had taken the place of a lowly Servant, acting only from and in
obedience to the Father. ([Phi 2:5-8](../../../bib/kjv/phi002.htm#005).md);
([Joh 5:19](../../../bib/kjv/joh005.htm#019).md); ([Joh
6:57](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#057).md); ([Joh
8:28](../../../bib/kjv/joh008.htm#028).md); ([Joh
8:54](../../../bib/kjv/joh008.htm#054).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Isa 41:8](../../../bib/kjv/isa041.htm#008).md).

that He might redeem a fallen race and a creation under the curse; ([Gen
3:17-19](../../../bib/kjv/gen003.htm#017).md); ([Rom
8:19-23](../../../bib/kjv/rom008.htm#019).md). Satan's one object in the
threefold temptation was to induce Christ to act from Himself, in
independency of His Father. The first two temptations were a challenge
to Christ from the god of this world to prove Himself indeed the Son of
God ([Mat 4:3-6](../../../bib/kjv/mat004.htm#003).md). The third was the
offer of the usurping prince of this world to divest himself of that
which rightfully belonged to Christ as Son of man and Son of David, on
the condition that He accept the sceptre on Satan's world-principles.

Compare ([Joh 18:36](../../../bib/kjv/joh018.htm#036).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Rev 13:8](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#008).md).

Christ defeated Satan by a means open to His humblest follower, the
intelligent use of the word of God ([Mat
4:4-7](../../../bib/kjv/mat004.htm#004).md). In his second temptation Satan
also used Scripture, but a promise available only to one in the path of
obedience. The scene give emphasis to the vital importance of "rightly
dividing the word of truth" ([Ti2
2:15](../../../bib/kjv/ti2002.htm#015).md).

